      "side": 1,
      "message": "There is now a design doc: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/docs/+/92631 , and the D-Bus contract is published as a companion phosphor-dbus-interfaces change: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/+/92632 (xyz.openbmc_project.PefManager and PefFilter). This change consumes exactly that contract. On the D-Bus handling: the translator is intentionally thin; the only state logic is provider-presence detection via the object mapper, so an absent provider returns Destination Unavailable (0xD3) instead of CC 0x00 with a stale payload.",
