      "writtenOn": "2026-07-22T17:31:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I would like to keep this. The OEM-action bit (0x10) is necessarily duplicated in the SEL matcher (pefActionsImplemented) because they live in separate recipes and cannot share a header. Each side pins its constant to the spec-defined bit with a static_assert, so a typo on either side fails that side\u0027s build instead of silently shipping a mask that advertises an action the consumer does not implement. Zero runtime cost.",
